                            <comment id="14153568" author="fhueske" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 19:01:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new Scala API supports &lt;tt&gt;crossWithTiny()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;crossWithHuge()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Looking at the implementation, I get the impression that all cross functions (&lt;tt&gt;cross&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;crossWithHuge&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;crossWithTiny&lt;/tt&gt;) are execute the same way.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aljoscha&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aljoscha&quot;&gt;aljoscha&lt;/a&gt; can you check if this issue can be closed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153588" author="hsaputra" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 19:14:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shall I assign it to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aljoscha&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aljoscha&quot;&gt;aljoscha&lt;/a&gt; as part of the new Scala API work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154393" author="aljoscha" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 05:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, they are all executed the same way. Exactly how it is done in the Java API.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154554" author="fhueske" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 08:19:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated this JIRA to fix the &lt;tt&gt;crossWith&lt;/tt&gt; hints in the Java and Scala API.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14269790" author="stephanewen" created="Thu, 8 Jan 2015 18:12:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed via 0954c4e521fafb0f1ecb7ae409bfc9ffbdfae51d&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
